  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6777.62 sitting just 2 points below the flip strike at 6779 and maximum positive gamma wall at 6780, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 6780 while providing buying support near the 6770 negative gamma pocket. The massive 411B total GEX and concentrated positive gamma walls at 6780/6785/6775 create a tight trading range with dealers acting as stabilizers, dampening volatility through mean-reverting flows. The gex_surge event combined with 124.5% five-minute GEX changes suggests dealers are rapidly adjusting hedges, likely selling gamma into any strength above 6779-6780.\n\nKey levels: 6770 (dealer buying), 6779 flip strike, and 6780 maximum resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect tight range-bound action between 6770-6785 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
